comment.returns: The position of the first occurance of the match string as a number, or `-1` if it is not found. On failure returns `-1`.

comment.shortText: Find the position of the last instance of one string in another.
comment.returns: The position of the last occurance of the match string as a number, or `-1` if it is not found. On failure returns `-1`.

comment.text: The string you are searching for

comment.shortText: Check to see if a string matches a regular expression
comment.returns:
A `false` if there is no match or regular expression match array where the first
                   item is the complete match and each subsequent iteam are the captured groups.
                   On failure returns `false`

comment.text: The regular expression to test the input string with
Any regular expression options to use (defaults to 'gi')

comment.shortText: Split up a string by a given delimeter
comment.returns: An array of strings. On failure returns an empty array.

comment.shortText: Gets a portion of a string from a starting point to a given length
comment.returns: A subportion of the input string. On failure returns an empty string.

tags.text:
```
{{substr "Hello, my name is E. Honda. How are you?" 18 8}}
output => "E. Honda"
```

comment.text: The point in the string to start from. The first character is `0`

comment.shortText: Gets a portion of a string from a starting point to an end point
comment.returns: A subportion of the input string. On failure returns an empty string.

tags.text:
```
{{substring "Hello, my name is E. Honda. How are you?" 18 26}}
output => "E. Honda"
```

comment.text: The point in the string to start from. The first character is `0`
